  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30319&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for`
  line `all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution, powers and functions of the authorities of the University, as may be`
  line `constituted from time to time;`
  line
  line `(b) the appointment and continuance in office of the members of the authorities, the filling up`
  line `of vacancies, and all other matters relating to the authorities for which it may be necessary or`
  line `desirable to provide;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment, powers and duties of the officers of the University and their emoluments;`
  line
  line `(d) the appointment of teachers, academic staff and other employees of the University and`
  line `their emoluments;`
  line
  line `(e) the appointment of teachers and academic staff working in any other University or`
  line `organisation for a specific period for undertaking a joint project;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions of service of employees including provision for pension, insurance and`
  line `provident fund, the manner of termination of service and disciplinary action;`
  line
  line `(g) the principles governing the seniority of service of employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for arbitration in cases of dispute between employees or students and the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for appeal to the Board by any employee or student against the action of any`
  line `officer or authority of the University;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and abolition of departments, centres, colleges and institutions;`
  line
  line `(k) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(l) the withdrawal of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions;`
  line
  line `(m) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(n) the delegation of powers vested in the authorities or officers of the University;`
  line
  line `(o) the maintenance of discipline among the employees and students; and`
  line
  line `(p) all other matters which are to be, or may be, prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (30320)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Statutes how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30320&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes are those set out in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may from time to time make Statutes or may amend or repeal the Statutes referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not make, amend or repeal any Statute affecting the status, powers`
  line `or constitution of any authority of the University until such authority has been given an opportunity of`
  line `expressing an opinion in writing on the proposed changes, and any opinion so expressed shall be`
  line `considered by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Statute or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require the assent of the Visitor`
  line `who may assent thereto or withhold assent therefrom or remit it to the Board for consideration.`
  line
  line `(4) A Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless it`
  line `has been assented to by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may amend or`
  line `repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section (1) during the period of three years immediately after the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may direct the`
  line `University to make provisions in the Statutes in respect of any matter specified by him and if the`
  line `Board is unable to implement such direction within sixty days of its receipt, the Visitor may, after`
  line `considering the reasons, if any, communicated by the Board for its inability to comply with such`
  line `direction, make or amend the Statutes suitably.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (30321)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make Ordinances`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30321&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and Statutes, the`
  line `Ordinances may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students to the University and their enrolment as such;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(c) the medium of instruction and examination;`
  line
  line `(d) the award of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions, the`
  line `qualifications for the same and the means to be taken relating to the granting and obtaining of the`
  line same;
  line
  line `(e) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the University and for admission to the`
  line `examinations, degrees, diplomas and certificates of the University;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions for award of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of examinations, including the term of office and manner of appointment and`
  line `duties of examining bodies, examiners and moderators;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions of residence of the students;`
  line
  line `(i) the special arrangements, if any, which may be made for the residence, discipline and`
  line `teaching of women students and the prescribing of special courses of studies for them;`
  line
  line `(j) the appointment and emoluments of employees other than those for whom provision has`
  line `been made in the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(k) the establishment of special centres, specialised laboratories and other committees;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of co-operation and collaboration with other Universities and authorities`
  line `including learned bodies or associations;`
  line
  line `(m) the creation, composition and functions of any other body which is considered necessary`
  line `for improving the academic life of the University;`
  line
  line `(n) such other terms and conditions of service of teachers and other academic staff as are not`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(o) the management of colleges and institutions established by the University;`
  line
  line `(p) the setting up of a mechanism for redressal of grievances of employees; and`
  line
  line `(q) all other matters which by this Act or the Statutes may be provided for by the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) The first Ordinances shall be made by the Vice-Chancellor with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and the Ordinances so made may be amended or repealed at any time by the`
  line `Board in the manner prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (30322)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Regulations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30322&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The authorities of the University may make Regulations, consistent with this`
  line `Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances for the conduct of their own business and that of the Committees`
  line `appointed by them and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances in the manner`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (30323)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30323&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the`
  line `direction of the Board, which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the University`
  line `towards the fulfilment of its objects and shall be submitted to the Board on or after such date as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Statutes and the Board shall consider the report in its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall submit the annual report to the Visitor along with its comments, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the annual report as prepared under sub-section (1) shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both the Houses`
  line `of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (30324)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Annual accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30324&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual accounts of the University shall be prepared under the`
  line `directions of the Board and shall, once at least every year and at intervals of not more than fifteen`
  line `months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or by such persons as he may`
  line `authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the annual accounts together with the audit report thereon shall be submitted to the`
  line `Board and the Visitor along with the observations of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Any observations made by the Visitor on the annual accounts shall be brought to the notice of`
  line `the Board and observations of the Board, if any, shall be submitted to the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the annual accounts together with the audit report as submitted to the Visitor, shall`
  line `also be submitted to the Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be`
  line `laid before both the Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(5) The audited annual accounts after having been laid before both the Houses of Parliament shall`
  line `be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (30325)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Conditions of service of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30325&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employee of the University shall be`
  line `appointed under a written contract which shall be lodged with the University and a copy of which`
  line `shall be furnished to the employee concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of the contract between the University and any employee shall, at the`
  line `request of the employee, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed`
  line `by the Board, one member nominated by the employee concerned and an umpire appointed by the`
  line Visitor.
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Tribunal shall be final, and no suit shall lie in any civil court in respect of`
  line `the matters decided by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Every request made by the employee under sub-section (2) shall be deemed to be a submission`
  line `to arbitration upon the terms of this section within the meaning of the Arbitration and Conciliation`
  line `Act, 1996 (26 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure for regulating the work of the Tribunal shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (30326)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure of appeal and arbitration in disciplinary cases against students.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30326&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any`
  line `student or candidate for an examination whose name has been removed from the rolls of the`
  line `University by the orders or resolution of the Vice-Chancellor, Discipline Committee or Examination`
  line `Committee, as the case may be, and who has been debarred from appearing at the examinations of the`
  line `University for more than one year, may, within ten days of the date of receipt of such orders or copy`
  line `of such resolution by him, appeal to the Board and the Board may confirm, modify or reverse the`
  line `decision of the Vice-Chancellor or the Committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of any disciplinary action taken by the University against a student`
  line `shall, at the request of such student, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration and the provisions of subsections (2), (3), (4) and (5) of section 32 shall, as far as may be, apply to a reference made under this`
  line sub-section.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (30327)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Right to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30327&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every employee or student of the University or of a college or institution`
  line `maintained by the University shall, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, have a right to`
  line `appeal, within such time as may be prescribed by the Statutes, to the Board against the decision of any`
  line `officer or authority of the University or any college or an institution, as the case may be, and`
  line `thereupon the Board may confirm, modify or reverse the decision appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (30328)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Provident and pension funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30328&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The University shall constitute for the benefit of its`
  line `employees such provident or pension fund or provide such insurance schemes as it may deem fit in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such provident fund or pension fund has been so constituted, the Central Government`
  line `may, if deem fit, declare that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925), shall`
  line `apply to such fund, as if it were a Government provident fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (30329)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Disputes as to constitution of University authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30329&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises as to whether`
  line `any person has been duly appointed as, or is entitled to be, a member of any authority of the`
  line `University, the matter shall be referred to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (30330)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Constitution of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30330&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Where any authority of the University is given power by this`
  line `Act or the Statutes to appoint Committees, such Committees shall, save as otherwise provided, consist of the members of the authority concerned and of such persons, if any, as the authority in each case`
  line `may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (30331)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Filling of casual vacancies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30331&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `All casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio`
  line `members) of any authority or other body of the University shall be filled, as soon as may be, by the`
  line `person or body who appoints or co-opts the member whose place has become vacant and the person or`
  line `body appointed or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be a member of such authority or body for the`
  line `residue of the term, for which the person whose place he fills would have been a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (30332)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Proceedings of University authorities not invalidated by vacancy`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30332&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings`
  line `of any authority of the University shall be invalid merely by reason of the existence of a vacancy or`
  line `vacancies among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (30333)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30333&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against the Board, Vice-Chancellor, any authority or officer or other employee of the`
  line `University for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (30334)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Mode of proof of University records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30334&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any receipt, application, notice, order,`
  line `proceeding, resolution of any authority or Committee of the University, or other documents in`
  line `possession of the University, or any entry in any register duly maintained by the University, if verified`
  line `by the Registrar, shall be received as prima facie evidence of such receipt, application, notice, order,`
  line `proceeding, resolution or documents or the existence of entry in the register and shall be admitted as`
  line `evidence of the matters and transactions therein where the original thereof would, if produced, have`
  line `been admissible in evidence, notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence`
  line `Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), or in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (30335)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Effect of establishment of University`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30335&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date of commencement of this`
  line Act,—
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the Rajendra Agricultural University in any contract or other instrument`
  line `shall be deemed as a reference to the University;`
  line
  line `(b) all property, movable and immovable, of or belonging to the Rajendra Agricultural`
  line `University shall vest in the University;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights and liabilities of the Rajendra Agricultural University shall be transferred to, and`
  line `be the rights and liabilities of, the University.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person permanently employed in the Rajendra Agricultural University immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Act who meets the requisite qualification and criteria of recruitment`
  line `in the University shall be provided an opportunity to be employed as such:`
  line
  line `Provided that every member of the academic staff and member of Faculty who does not meet the`
  line `requisite qualification and criteria shall be given an opportunity for two years to upgrade the`
  line `qualification and to meet the criteria:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every other person permanently employed shall be given an opportunity to`
  line `upgrade the qualification and to meet the criteria, in the manner provided by the Regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the tenure, remuneration, terms and conditions, rights and privileges as to`
  line `pension, leave, gratuity, provident fund and all other matters of every other person permanently`
  line `employed by the Rajendra Agricultural University shall be determined by the State Government of`
  line Bihar.
  line
  line `(3) All efforts shall be made by the State Government of Bihar to engage any surplus or`
  line `temporary academic staff, teacher, member of Faculty or other employee of the Rajendra Agricultural`
  line `University, by or against whom any dispute is pending.`
  line
  line `(4) Any dispute or litigation, the cause of action for which has arisen between any member of`
  line `academic staff, teacher, member of Faculty or other employee and the Rajendra Agricultural`
  line `University before the commencement of this Act shall be instituted, prosecuted or continued between`
  line `the academic staff, teacher, member of Faculty or other employee and the Rajendra Agricultural`
  line `University, as if this Act had not been enacted, and all such cases shall be managed by a special cell to be constituted by the State Government of Bihar and all expenses relating to the management of such`
  line `cases including any compensation payable to any person thereof shall be borne by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(5) Any academic course, programme or scheme as on the date of commencement of the Act shall`
  line `be continued, till the completion of the course, programme or scheme with such modifications as the`
  line `University may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government of Bihar and the University shall bear the proportionate cost of pension`
  line `and other liabilities of every academic staff, teacher, member of Faculty or other employee,`
  line `proportionate to the extent of the respective period of service of the person and the State Government`
  line `shall provide its contribution to the University which may discharge any liability on account of this.`
  line
  line `(7) Any matter relating to permanent record of students, teachers, academic staff, Faculty and`
  line `every other employee shall be provided by Regulations.`
  line
  line `(8) Pension and all other post-retirement benefits including medical benefits of every academic`
  line `staff, teacher, faculty member and every other employee who has superannuated before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall be borne by the State Government of Bihar, the payment of which`
  line `shall be made through the University and shall be governed by the rules relating thereof made by the`
  line `State Government of Bihar in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(9) The retirement age of every teacher, academic staff, Faculty and every other employee of the`
  line `University shall be governed by any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(10) Any matter governing the conditions of service relating to the teacher, academic staff,`
  line `Faculty and every other employee for which no provision has been made in this Act, shall be`
  line `determined by the corresponding provisions made by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (30336)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30336&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provision of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient`
  line `for removing the difficulties:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (30337)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30337&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, and the`
  line Statutes,—
  line
  line `(a) the first Chancellor and the first Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor and`
  line `shall hold office for a term of five years;`
  line
  line `(b) the first Registrar and the first Comptroller shall be appointed by the Visitor and each of`
  line `the said officers shall hold office for a term of three years;`
  line
  line `(c) the first members of the Board shall be nominated by the Visitor and shall hold office for a`
  line `term of three years;`
  line
  line `(d) the first members of the Academic Council shall be nominated by the Visitor and shall`
  line `hold office for a term of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any vacancy occurs in the above offices or authorities, the same shall be filled`
  line `by appointment or nomination, as the case may be, by the Visitor, and the person so appointed or`
  line `nominated shall hold office for so long as the officer or member in whose place he is appointed or`
  line `nominated would have held office, if such vacancy had not occurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (30338)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal of Bihar Agricultural University Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30338&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bihar Agricultural University`
  line `Act, 1987 (Bihar Act 8 of 1988), in so far as it relates to the Rajendra Agricultural University, Pusa,`
  line `Bihar is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal,—`
  line
  line `(a) all appointments made, orders issued, degrees and other academic distinctions conferred,`
  line `diplomas and certificates awarded, privileges granted or other things done under the Bihar`
  line `Agricultural University Act, 1987 (Bihar Act 8 of 1988), in so far as it relates to the Rajendra`
  line `Agricultural University, Pusa, Bihar, shall be deemed to have been respectively made, issued,`
  line `conferred, awarded, granted or done under the corresponding provisions of this Act, and, except`
  line `as otherwise provided by or under this Act or the Statues, continue in force unless and until they`
  line `are superseded by any order made under this Act or the Statues; and`
  line
  line `(b) all proceedings of Selection Committees for the appointment or promotions of teachers`
  line `that took place before the commencement of this Act and all actions of the Governing Body in`
  line `respect of the recommendations of such Selection Committees where no orders of appointment on`
  line `the basis thereof were passed before the commencement of this Act, in so far as it relates to`
  line `Rajendra Agricultural University, shall, notwithstanding that the procedure for selection has been`
  line `modified by this Act, be deemed to have been valid but further proceeding in connection with`
  line `such pending selections shall be taken in accordance with the provisions of this Act and be`
  line `continued from the stage where they stood immediately before such commencement, except if the`
  line `concerned authorities take, with the approval of the Visitor, a decision to the contrary.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (30339)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Statutes, Ordinances and Regulations to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191&sectionId=30339&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_47_00006_201632_1517807328191
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the Statutes, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses`
  line `agree that the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or`
  line `Regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that Statute, Ordinance or Regulation.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make Statutes, Ordinances or Regulations shall include the power to give`
  line `retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the Statutes,`
  line `Ordinances or Regulations or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such`
  line `Statutes, Ordinances or Regulations may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
